UID:5562-1778936400-1778947200@bloomspinweave.org
SUMMARY:Beginning Drop Spindle Spinning given by Nelly DeVault
DESCRIPTION:May 16\, 2026 1:00 – 4:00 PM. \nParticipants will learn to make yarn of the oldest fiber arts tool in the world! When you leave\, you will take your first yarn with you. \n$55 BSWG members \n$65 non-BSWG members students (includes one-year guild membership) \n$85 non-BSWG members (includes one-year guild membership) \nClass size 3-8 \nMaterials provided by the instructor for an additional fee of $5. You may choose to buy your spindle from the instructor for $15\, borrow one for class or bring your own!  Spinning fiber provided. \nNo experience necessary. \nRegister Here \n\n           Download QR
URL:https://bloomspinweave.org/event/beginning-drop-spindle-spinning-given-by-nelly-devault
LOCATION:Fiber Arts Center\, College Mall\, Bloomington\, 3038 East Third Street\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47401\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Fiber Arts Guild Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bloomspinweave.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/DeVault-Beginning-Drop-Spindle-scaled.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Guild":MAILTO:educationbswg@gmail.com, newsletterbswg@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
