UID:5513-1780144200-1780158600@bloomspinweave.org
SUMMARY:Introduction to Two Color Brioche Knitting with Megan Bube
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, May 30th 12:30 – 4:30 PM \nCurious about learning brioche knitting? Come join us for this one-day introductory class! Participants will learn two-color brioche knitting in both flat and in-the-round\, including a few common increase and decrease stitches found in brioche patterns. Students are expected to know intermediate/advanced knitting techniques such as knitting in the round\, slipped stitches\, and how to use a cable needle. \n  \n$55 – BSWG members \n$65 – non-BSWG student members (includes one-year guild student membership) \n$85 – non-BSWG members (includes one-year guild membership) \nClass size 2-6 students \n  \nStudents should bring the following: Two ~10-gram balls of DK or worsted weight yarn in 2 contrasting colors (recommended to use a light and a dark or a variegated and a solid color)\, size US4 or US5 circular needles or DPNs\, and a cable needle. \nTo register\, click here. \n\n           Download QR
URL:https://bloomspinweave.org/event/introduction-to-two-color-brioche-knitting-with-megan-bube
LOCATION:Fiber Arts Center\, College Mall\, Bloomington\, 3038 East Third Street\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47401\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Fiber Arts Guild Calendar
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bloomspinweave.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/25-Brioche-Megan.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Guild":MAILTO:educationbswg@gmail.com, newsletterbswg@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
