SUMMARY:Beginning Crochet with Mary Schwitzer
DESCRIPTION:Have you been wanting to learn crochet? Come learn the fundamental stitches and techniques. We will practice these techniques by making small decorative mats that you can take home and enjoy. \nSaturday\, June 27th\, 10:00 am – 2:00 pm. Bring a lunch or grab something in the mall. \n$50 BSWG Member\n$60 non-BSWG Member Student (includes one-year guild membership)\n$80 non-BSWG Member (includes one-year guild membership) \nClass size 1-6 students \nThe instructor will send the supply list to students. \nNo experience is required. \nRegister here. \n\n           Download QR
URL:https://bloomspinweave.org/event/beginning-crochet-by-mary-schwitzer-2
LOCATION:Fiber Arts Center\, College Mall\, Bloomington\, 3038 East Third Street\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47401\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bloomington Spinners and Weavers Fiber Arts Guild Calendar
